         <abstract>
            <p>Let $N &gt; 1$. We present a method for multiplying two integers (called $N$-residues) modulo $N$ while avoiding division by $N. N$-residues are represented in a nonstandard way, so this method is useful only if several computations are done modulo one $N$. The addition and subtraction algorithms are unchanged.</p>
          </abstract>
